#############################################################################
# This recipe describes the process one goes through to add/edit 
# a user on our pmwiki documentation software (as accessed here:
# http://almost.zfin.org/new_doc).
#
#
#############################################################################

In order to add or update passwords for logging into the pmwiki documentation
at ZFIN, you must be able to sudo to the user "zfishweb."

Then execute the following commands:

% cd /private/etc/apache/pmwiki/
% sudo -u zfishweb newPass.sh [username]

you will then be prompted to enter the password for the new user twice.

Also, if you cntl-C out of the program, it leaves the htpasswd file writable 
by zfishweb...so don't make my mistake and do that.


